/* first way */

1. If you know the ESSID of the Wi-Fi network you wish to connect to, move to the next step, otherwise issue the command below to scan available Wi-Fi networks again.

$ sudo iw wlp1s0 scan

2. And lastly, connect to the wi-fi network using following command, where gaurav (Wi-Fi network SSID) and Gaurav@0563 (password/pre-shared key).

$ nmcli dev wifi connect gaurav password Gaurav@0563




/* second way */

1. To list all the network interface 

$ sudo ip link show 

2. To connect the internet 

$ sudo ip link set  <interface-name> up 

3. To disconnect the internet 

$sudo ip link set <interface-name> down


/* Third way */
 

